---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "header"
description: "Introductory content for its nearest sectioning ancestor. Contains headings, logos, navigation, search forms, or other introductory elements."
elementName: header
category: native
nativeGroup: Sectioning
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/header/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/header/
---

{% set defaultCode %}<header>
  <h2>Page Title</h2>
  <p>A brief description of the page content.</p>
</header>{% endset %}

{% set siteCode %}<header class="site">
  <strong>Brand</strong>
  <nav class="horizontal pills" aria-label="Site navigation">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Products</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>{% endset %}

{% set pageCode %}<header class="page">
  <h1>Documentation</h1>
  <p>Learn how to use Vanilla Breeze in your projects.</p>
</header>
<p>Page content begins here...</p>{% endset %}

{% set cardCode %}<layout-card>
  <header class="card">
    <h3>Card Title</h3>
  </header>
  <p>Card content goes here...</p>
</layout-card>{% endset %}

{% set stickyCode %}<header class="sticky site">
  <strong>Sticky Header</strong>
  <nav class="horizontal pills">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Link 1</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Link 2</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>{% endset %}

{% set centeredCode %}<header class="centered">
  <h1>Welcome to Our Site</h1>
  <p>Building the future of web development,
  one component at a time.</p>
</header>{% endset %}

{% set compactCode %}<header class="compact site">
  <strong>Brand</strong>
  <nav class="horizontal minimal">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Docs</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">API</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>{% endset %}

  <section>
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> element for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Site header with logo, navigation, and search</li>
      <li>Page header with title and breadcrumbs</li>
      <li>Article header with title, author, and publication date</li>
      <li>Section headers with title and description</li>
      <li>Card headers with title and actions</li>
    </ul>
    <p>A page can have multiple header elements: one for the site and additional ones within articles, sections, or other content.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <p>Basic header without additional styling.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-default.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/default" title="Default header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Default header">{{ defaultCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.site</h3>
    <p>Full-width site header with flexbox layout.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-site.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/site" title="Site header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Site header">{{ siteCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.page</h3>
    <p>Page header with bottom border and spacing.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-page.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/page" title="Page header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Page header">{{ pageCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.card</h3>
    <p>Card header with bottom border.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-card.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/card" title="Card header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Card header">{{ cardCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.sticky</h3>
    <p>Sticky header that remains at the top during scroll.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-sticky.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/sticky" title="Sticky header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Sticky header">{{ stickyCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.centered</h3>
    <p>Centered header for landing pages.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-centered.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/centered" title="Centered header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Centered header">{{ centeredCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.compact</h3>
    <p>Compact header with reduced padding and smaller text.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/header-compact.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/header/compact" title="Compact header" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Compact header">{{ compactCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variants</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Class</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.site</code></td>
          <td>Flexbox layout with space-between, padding, and bottom border</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.page</code></td>
          <td>Bottom border and margin for page title headers</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.card</code></td>
          <td>Padding with bottom border for card headers</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.sticky</code></td>
          <td>Fixed to top with z-index and background</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.transparent</code></td>
          <td>Absolute positioning with transparent background for hero overlays</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.centered</code></td>
          <td>Centered text and auto margins for children</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.compact</code></td>
          <td>Reduced padding and smaller font size</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The document's main header becomes a banner landmark (only when not nested)</li>
      <li>Include skip links at the start of the header to bypass navigation</li>
      <li>Use <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> with <code>aria-label</code> to identify navigation regions</li>
      <li>Sticky headers should not obscure content when users navigate with keyboard</li>
      <li>Ensure transparent headers maintain sufficient contrast with background</li>
      <li>Consider <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> for sticky header animations</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

